The paper presents a language for low-level programming and verification, which involves type checking and program verification. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the memory model and control required for writing efficient low-level security-critical code, which suggests that it may also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
